org.naregi.rns.client
Class RNSKeyValue

java.lang.Object
  org.naregi.rns.client.RNSKeyValue

public class RNSKeyValue
extends java.lang.Object

Key/Value operations to RNS Metadata. The key/value mapping is following format in RNS Metadata. 

 <rnskv key="key">value</rnskv>
This Metadata usage is not a specification in RNS 1.1. This does not implement java.util.Map interface.

keySet

public java.util.Set<java.lang.String> keySet()
                                       throws RNSError
Returns a java.util.Set view of the keys contained in this map. The set is backed by the map, so changes to the map are reflected in the set, and vice-versa. If the map is modified while an iteration over the set is in progress (except through the iterator's own remove operation), the results of the iteration are undefined. The set supports element removal, which removes the corresponding mapping from the map, via the Iterator.remove, Set.remove, removeAll, retainAll, and clear operations. It does not support the add or addAll operations.

Returns:
a set view of the keys contained in this Metadata
Throws:
RNSError
